        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="30" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Walter S. Robertson</persName> to
                        General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-21">21 August
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. On 19 August the Three Commissioners agreed to direct Sub-Team 25 to proceed
                    immediately to the Hsiang Ho area via Anping to investigate alleged conflicts in
                    that area. NG and CCP<note n="76" xml:id="d30fn76">National Government and
                        Chinese Communist Party, respectively.</note> Commissioners offered safe
                    conduct for the team.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
